From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harmen Stoppels <harmen@stoppels.ch>
Date: Thu, 12 Jun 2026 16:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] 0002: tree-ssa-ccp avoid nested 16B-struct-return call
 (tcc spill bug)

tcc 0.9.27 (AArch64) miscompiles set_lattice_value's
  new_val.mask = double_int_ior (new_val.mask,
                                 double_int_ior (old_val->mask, diff));
It assigns the same stack spill slot to the saved &new_val.mask pointer
(new_val is a 32-byte by-reference struct param) and to a scalar spilled
while evaluating the inner double_int_ior (high half of old_val->mask).
The scalar store clobbers the pointer; the later reload dereferences a
data value -> SIGSEGV inside the tree-ccp pass (crashes the tcc-built cc1
while compiling libgcc2.c's __cmpti2/__ucmpti2).

Splitting the inner call into a named temporary removes the live-range
overlap and makes tcc emit correct code. Functionally identical.

See bugs/tcc-aarch64-nested-struct-return-spill.md for the full analysis
and a self-contained reproducer.
---
 gcc/tree-ssa-ccp.c | 5 +++--
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/gcc/tree-ssa-ccp.c
+++ b/gcc/tree-ssa-ccp.c
@@ -448,10 +448,11 @@
       && TREE_CODE (old_val->value) == INTEGER_CST)
     {
       double_int diff;
+      double_int tmp_mask;
       diff = double_int_xor (tree_to_double_int (new_val.value),
 			     tree_to_double_int (old_val->value));
-      new_val.mask = double_int_ior (new_val.mask,
-				     double_int_ior (old_val->mask, diff));
+      tmp_mask = double_int_ior (old_val->mask, diff);
+      new_val.mask = double_int_ior (new_val.mask, tmp_mask);
     }

   gcc_assert (valid_lattice_transition (*old_val, new_val));
